Basic size
```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}]
```

Grid, one auto, one explicit
```
Grid[{{
    ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}],
    ContourPlot[{x^2+y^2 == 1, x^2-y^2==0.5} , {x,-2,2},{y,-2,2}, ImageSize->{100,100}]
}}]
```

Basic size again

```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}]
```

Explicit, just a number

```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}, ImageSize->100]
```

Explicit, not square
```
ContourPlot[x^2 - y^2, {x, -2, 2}, {y, -2, 2}, ImageSize->{100,200}]
```
